      <h1 class='title'>Iraq: Campaign Medal</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='lords-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 23 February 2004 vol 658 c4WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_4ws' title='Col. 4WS &mdash; HL Deb 23 February 2004 vol 658 c4WS' name='column_4ws' href='#column_4ws' rel='bookmark'>4WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0658P0-06531'>
        <a name='S5LV0658P0_20040223_LWS_6'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-william-bach' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0658P0_20040223_LWS_6' title='Link to this speech by Mr William Bach' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-william-bach" title="Mr William Bach">Lord Bach</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S5LV0658P0-06531">My right honourable friend the Minister of State for Defence (Mr Adam Ingram) has made the following Written Ministerial Statement.</p><p id="S5LV0658P0-06532">I am pleased to announce that Her Majesty has graciously approved the detailed qualifying criteria for the award of a campaign medal for recent operations in Iraq. I have laid the Command Paper instituting the Iraq Campaign Medal in Parliament today.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
